Saucy Roasted Potatoes (Serves 8) The small, round, yellow-fleshed potatoes sold in mesh bags are perfect for this rendition of Spanish patatas bravas. Ingredients 680g very small yellow-fleshed round potatoes 3 tbs extra-virgin olive oil coarse or flaky sea salt crushed red pepper flakes 1/4 cup mayonnaise 3 tbs red pepper sauce Method Rinse and drain the potatoes. Spread them on a rimmed baking sheet; drizzle with the olive oil and sprinkle with a pinch or two of salt and pepper flakes. Roast in a 230degree oven for 8 to 10 minutes, or until just tender. Meanwhile, whisk together the mayonnaise and red pepper sauce. Transfer the potatoes to a serving bowl. Top with spoonfuls of the mayo-pepper sauce and an optional sprinkling of chopped chives. The Washington Post